        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 3:43PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 343 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinecliffe, or 29 miles northwest of Denver, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Arvada, southwestern Boulder, Nederland, Central
City, Black Hawk, Pinecliffe, Rollinsville, Wallstreet, Crisman,
Aspen Springs, Salina, Eldorado Springs, Summerville, Gold Hill,
Sunshine, White Ranch Open Space, Rocky Flats, Eldora, Crescent
Village and Caribou.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
